<paragraph blockId="8.[677,1210,1484,1699]" box="[677,931,1484,1510]" pageId="8" pageNumber="79">CONSERVATION STATUS</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="79" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[677,1210,1484,1699]" pageId="8" pageNumber="79">
<taxonomicName box="[677,836,1515,1541]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Olacaceae" genus="Olax" kingdom="Plantae" order="Santalales" pageId="8" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capuronii">
<emphasis box="[677,836,1515,1541]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="79">Olax capuronii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has not been collected inside any formally protected areas. The EOO for the species is 
<quantity box="[751,839,1578,1604]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.12" pageId="8" pageNumber="79" unit="km" value="212.0">212 km</quantity>
2 and the AOO is 
<quantity box="[1051,1139,1578,1604]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="79" unit="km" value="400.0">400 km</quantity>
2 (grid cell size 10 × 
<quantity box="[827,904,1610,1636]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="79" unit="km" value="10.0">10 km</quantity>
). These figures indicate that 
<taxonomicName box="[678,815,1641,1667]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Olacaceae" genus="Olax" kingdom="Plantae" order="Santalales" pageId="8" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capuronii">
<emphasis box="[678,697,1641,1667]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="79">O</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[712,815,1642,1667]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="79">capuronii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be considered Endangered (EN B1ab + B2 ab).
</paragraph>
